<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="366" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[140,1108,553,756]" pageId="9" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis box="[185,337,589,615]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="366">Colon politum</emphasis>
is newly recorded in Labrador and in Atlantic 
<collectingCountry box="[843,931,589,615]" name="Canada" pageId="9" pageNumber="366">Canada</collectingCountry>
. It is a Holarctic species previously recorded from Alaska east to 
<collectingRegion box="[662,814,624,650]" country="Canada" name="Saskatchewan" pageId="9" pageNumber="366">Saskatchewan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peck and Stephan" box="[828,1095,624,651]" firstAuthor="Peck" pageId="9" pageNumber="366" pagination="667 - 741" refId="ref23890" refString="Peck SB, Stephan K (1996) A revision of the genus Colon Herbst (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Coloninae) of North America. The Canadian Entomologist 128: 667 - 741." type="journal article" year="1996">Peck and Stephan 1996</bibRefCitation>
). This record represents a range extension of 
<quantity box="[616,725,659,685]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="366" unit="km" value="2.7">2,700 km</quantity>
to the east within North America. No specific information is available on the bionomics of this species. Many species of 
<emphasis box="[140,203,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="366">Colon</emphasis>
are believed to be associated with subterranean fungi (
<bibRefCitation author="Peck and Stephan" box="[802,1068,729,756]" firstAuthor="Peck" pageId="9" pageNumber="366" pagination="667 - 741" refId="ref23890" refString="Peck SB, Stephan K (1996) A revision of the genus Colon Herbst (Coleoptera: Leiodidae: Coloninae) of North America. The Canadian Entomologist 128: 667 - 741." type="journal article" year="1996">Peck and Stephan 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
